file=Brand Studio/rio/operational/skill/rio-skill-routing.md · h=name: rio-skill-routing\ntype: operational/skill\nstatus: consolidated from the "Boundaries" sections of rio's skill files — no new logic invented\nassigned_agent: rio (Brand Studio / Ads)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=Rio's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/rio-commands.md`.\n · wif:Where Identity Fits=Rio has no identity — spark holds Brand Studio's. Universal-only principles.\n · ts:The Stack=```\nsales-retargeting        (STRATEGY — what to retarget, segmentation, sequencing, · tb=\|                   channel selection; honesty gotchas built in) · ts:The Stack=ad-platform-mechanics    (PLATFORM LAYER — durable principles static; volatile specs · tb=\|                   in dated per-platform playbooks; policy lines are law) · ts:The Stack=ad-thresholds            (GUARDRAILS — daily patrol vs config rules: KILL/SCALE/ESCALATE\nrecommendations, everything logged, kai reconciles)\n```\n\nEvery campaign action touches all three: strategy says what, mechanics says how-on-this-platform, thresholds says whether it lives.\n · hr:Handoff Rules=- **board → rio**: the budget envelope comes from board's fiduciary gate; rio patrols within it; envelope-crossing changes go back through board. Ad spend is spend.\n- **pulse → rio**: the hooks register's proven organic posts are the paid-creative shortlist — organic evidence before paid spend.\n- **pixel → rio**: ad creative production (spark-gated like everything). **lena**: ad copy through voice + humanic; email-retargeting sequences are lena's to design.\n- **kai ↔ rio**: kai's independent numbers reconcile platform-reported ROAS; reconciliations refresh the playbooks; rio never grades its own homework.\n- **nate ↔ rio**: new-channel and creative *experiments* are nate's (ICE backlog, A/B discipline); a proven experiment graduates to rio as a standing campaign.\n- **Policy/jurisdiction**: violating requests are refused and flagged (sentinel-adjacent), never optimized.\n · p:Precedence="Should we run ads / what do we retarget" → strategy. "Set up / why is delivery weird" → mechanics. "Scale/kill/how are they doing" → thresholds. Ambiguous → which of what/how/whether.\n · f:=No connectors → operator exports on cadence, as-of dated. No configured rules → NOT CONFIGURED + a proposal session, never defaults.\n